===Etymology===
From [[w:French language|French]][[category:French derivations]] [[vis]] (meaning ''a [[screw]], winding stairs''), [[w:Old French|Old French]][[Category:Old French derivations]] vis, viz, from [[w:Latin|Latin]][[Category:Latin derivations]] [[vitis]] (meaning ''a [[vine]])''; probably akin to [[w:English language|English]][[Category:English derivations]] [[withy]].

===Noun===
'''vise'''
#An [[instrument]] consisting of two [[jaw]]s, closing by a screw, [[lever]], [[cam]], or the like, for holding work, as in filing. Also written [[vice]]. 


<!--from Webster:

      


 Vise (Page: 1613) Vise (?), n. [F. vis a screw, winding stairs, OF. vis, viz, fr. L. vitis a vine; probably akin to E. withy.] An instrument consisting of two jaws, closing by a screw, lever, cam, or the like, for holding work, as in filing. [Written also vice.] 

